Note:
AArch64 Assembly Generator - LIR to AArch64 ARM Syntax Assembly

THE MOST CRITICAL FILE IN THE AARCH64 BACKEND.

Translates LIR instructions (opcodes 30000-30999) with physical register assignments
into ARM syntax AArch64 assembly text. This is the primary code generation path for
the Runa compiler on AArch64 (Linux on ARM, macOS on Apple Silicon, etc.).

The generator processes an entire LIR module (collection of LIR functions), emitting:
- Function prologues (stp x29, x30, [sp, #-size]! / mov x29, sp / save callee-saved)
- Basic block labels
- Instruction-by-instruction translation of all LIR opcodes to AArch64 instructions
- Function epilogues (restore callee-saved / ldp x29, x30, [sp], #size / ret)
- String literals in .rodata section
- Global variable declarations in .data/.bss sections

ARM syntax conventions (AArch64 uses ARM/UAL syntax, NOT AT&T):
- Destination first: add x0, x1, x2 (x0 = x1 + x2)
- Register names NOT prefixed: x0, w0, sp, xzr, wzr, v0, d0, s0
- Immediates prefixed with #: #42, #0x1000
- Memory: [x0], [x0, #16], [x0, x1, lsl #3]
- No size suffixes (instruction mnemonic determines size: add for 64-bit, add w for 32-bit)

LIR Opcode to AArch64 Instruction Mapping:
  30000 NOP     -> nop
  30001 MOV     -> mov Xd, Xn  (or movz/movk for large immediates)
  30100 ADD     -> add Xd, Xn, Xm
  30101 SUB     -> sub Xd, Xn, Xm
  30102 IMUL    -> mul Xd, Xn, Xm
  30103 IDIV    -> sdiv Xd, Xn, Xm
  30104 MUL     -> mul Xd, Xn, Xm  (unsigned same as signed for lower result)
  30105 DIV     -> udiv Xd, Xn, Xm
  30106 NEG     -> neg Xd, Xn
  30200 AND     -> and Xd, Xn, Xm
  30201 OR      -> orr Xd, Xn, Xm
  30202 XOR     -> eor Xd, Xn, Xm
  30203 NOT     -> mvn Xd, Xn
  30204 TEST    -> tst Xn, Xm
  30300 SHL     -> lsl Xd, Xn, Xm
  30301 SHR     -> lsr Xd, Xn, Xm
  30302 SAR     -> asr Xd, Xn, Xm
  30400 CMP     -> cmp Xn, Xm
  30500 JMP     -> b label
  30501 JZ      -> b.eq label (Zero flag = Equal flag after CMP)
  30502 JNZ     -> b.ne label
  30503 JE      -> b.eq label
  30504 JNE     -> b.ne label
  30505 JL      -> b.lt label
  30506 JLE     -> b.le label
  30507 JG      -> b.gt label
  30508 JGE     -> b.ge label
  30509 JB      -> b.lo label (unsigned below)
  30510 JBE     -> b.ls label (unsigned below or same)
  30511 JA      -> b.hi label (unsigned above)
  30512 JAE     -> b.hs label (unsigned above or same)
  30520 CALL    -> bl target
  30521 CALL_I  -> blr Xn
  30522 RET     -> ret (returns via LR/X30)
  30523 SYSCALL -> svc #0
  30600 LOAD    -> ldr Xd, [Xn, #offset]
  30601 STORE   -> str Xs, [Xn, #offset]
  30602 LOAD8   -> ldrb Wd, [Xn, #offset]
  30603 LOAD16  -> ldrh Wd, [Xn, #offset]
  30604 LOAD32  -> ldr Wd, [Xn, #offset]
  30605 LOAD64  -> ldr Xd, [Xn, #offset]
  30606 STORE8  -> strb Ws, [Xn, #offset]
  30607 STORE16 -> strh Ws, [Xn, #offset]
  30608 STORE32 -> str Ws, [Xn, #offset]
  30609 STORE64 -> str Xs, [Xn, #offset]
  30120 FADD    -> fadd Dd, Dn, Dm
  30121 FSUB    -> fsub Dd, Dn, Dm
  30122 FMUL    -> fmul Dd, Dn, Dm
  30123 FDIV    -> fdiv Dd, Dn, Dm
  30125 FSQRT   -> fsqrt Dd, Dn
  30127 FMIN    -> fmin Dd, Dn, Dm
  30128 FMAX    -> fmax Dd, Dn, Dm
  30700 SEXT    -> sxtw Xd, Wn (sign extend 32->64) or sxtb/sxth
  30701 ZEXT    -> uxtw Xd, Wn (zero extend) or mov Wd, Wn (implicit zero-extend)
  30704 I2F     -> scvtf Dd, Xn
  30706 F2I     -> fcvtzs Xd, Dn
  30707 F32TOF64 -> fcvt Dd, Sn
  30708 F64TOF32 -> fcvt Sd, Dn

Dependencies:
- Imports machine_code_interface.runa for common output types and section constants
- Imports calling_convention.runa for AAPCS64 register info
- Imports layout.runa for memory allocation
- Imports list.runa for collection operations
- Imports string_core.runa for integer-to-string conversion
- Imports string_utils.runa for string building
:End Note

Import "compiler/backend/machine_code/common/machine_code_interface.runa" as MachineCode
Import "compiler/backend/machine_code/aarch64/calling_convention.runa" as CallingConv
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/dictionary.runa" as Dictionary
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/internal/string_utils.runa" as StringUtils

Note: ============================================================================
Note: AArch64 Assembly Generation Context
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
The AArch64AsmContext holds all state needed during assembly generation for a module.
It wraps the AssemblyOutput buffer and adds AArch64-specific tracking.
@End Reasoning

Type called "AArch64AsmContext":
    output as Integer                 Note: Pointer to AssemblyOutput
    config as Integer                 Note: Pointer to BackendConfig
    current_function as Integer       Note: Pointer to current LIRFunction being emitted
    convention as Integer             Note: Pointer to CallingConventionInfo for current function
    arena as Integer                  Note: Arena for temporary allocations during generation
    error_count as Integer            Note: Number of errors encountered during generation
    string_buffer as Integer          Note: Temporary string buffer for building instruction text
End Type

Note: Size: 7 fields * 8 bytes = 56 bytes per AArch64AsmContext

Note: ============================================================================
Note: AArch64 GPR Name Tables (ARM syntax - no prefix)
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
AArch64 uses two register naming schemes:
- X0-X30 for 64-bit operations (full 64-bit register)
- W0-W30 for 32-bit operations (lower 32 bits, upper 32 bits zeroed on write)
- SP for the stack pointer
- XZR/WZR for the zero register

Unlike x86_64 AT&T syntax which uses % prefix, ARM syntax uses bare register names.
@End Reasoning

Process called "get_gpr_name_64" that takes reg_id as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Returns the 64-bit ARM register name for a GPR (0-31)
    If reg_id is 0:
        Return "x0"
    End If
    If reg_id is 1:
        Return "x1"
    End If
    If reg_id is 2:
        Return "x2"
    End If
    If reg_id is 3:
        Return "x3"
    End If
    If reg_id is 4:
        Return "x4"
    End If
    If reg_id is 5:
        Return "x5"
    End If
    If reg_id is 6:
        Return "x6"
    End If
    If reg_id is 7:
        Return "x7"
    End If
    If reg_id is 8:
        Return "x8"
    End If
    If reg_id is 9:
        Return "x9"
    End If
    If reg_id is 10:
        Return "x10"
    End If
    If reg_id is 11:
        Return "x11"
    End If
    If reg_id is 12:
        Return "x12"
    End If
    If reg_id is 13:
        Return "x13"
    End If
    If reg_id is 14:
        Return "x14"
    End If
    If reg_id is 15:
        Return "x15"
    End If
    If reg_id is 16:
        Return "x16"
    End If
    If reg_id is 17:
        Return "x17"
    End If
    If reg_id is 18:
        Return "x18"
    End If
    If reg_id is 19:
        Return "x19"
    End If
    If reg_id is 20:
        Return "x20"
    End If
    If reg_id is 21:
        Return "x21"
    End If
    If reg_id is 22:
        Return "x22"
    End If
    If reg_id is 23:
        Return "x23"
    End If
    If reg_id is 24:
        Return "x24"
    End If
    If reg_id is 25:
        Return "x25"
    End If
    If reg_id is 26:
        Return "x26"
    End If
    If reg_id is 27:
        Return "x27"
    End If
    If reg_id is 28:
        Return "x28"
    End If
    If reg_id is 29:
        Return "x29"
    End If
    If reg_id is 30:
        Return "x30"
    End If
    If reg_id is 31:
        Return "sp"
    End If
    If reg_id is 65:
        Return "xzr"
    End If
    Return "x0"
End Process

